{
  "texts": [
    "However, like research software, data sets should best 'be cited on the same basis as any other research product such as a paper or a book' [Druskat, 2022].",
    "Proper citing of data sets facilitates research transparency and ensures credit and accountability on the part of the data set producers [Ball and Duke, 2015].",
    "Metadata fields that should be part of any data set citation, if known, include author, publication date, title, version, resource type, publisher, identifier, and location.",
    "In parallel to data sets, the 'Item Type: Software' could be used for referencing ATR models, as is suggested on the Zotero forum.",
    "foot_13 This 'Item Type' requests information such as title, programmer, abstract, series, version and date, programming language, URL, and rights."
  ]
}